      "writtenOn": "2019-09-23T16:27:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done, although that article is focused on concurrent updates to the same object, and it\u0027s not clear to me whether contention would be a problem for starting up snapshot iterators (I would hope not).   FTR this is definitely a problem for transactions in Firestore: the client lib waits for a fixed amount of time before retrying, so two poorly timed transactions which modify the same document can get stuck in a fail+retry loop, until they time out.  If they use the same timeout, this can continue ~forever.  We should probably add slightly randomized timeout support to the go/firestore package.",
      "parentUuid": "5a46b01f_0396e212",
